uk.co.brightec.ratetheapp

Class DefaultOnUserSelectedRatingListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.brightec.ratetheapp.DefaultOnUserSelectedRatingListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RateTheApp.OnUserSelectedRatingListener

    public class DefaultOnUserSelectedRatingListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements RateTheApp.OnUserSelectedRatingListener
    The default OnRatingChangeListener that offers to take the user to the play store if a good rating was given, otherwise it prompts the user to email the app developer to provide feedback.

      • createDefaultInstance

        public static DefaultOnUserSelectedRatingListener createDefaultInstance(java.lang.String emailTo)
        The creates a default instance of this OnUserSelectedRatingListener. Override the string resources to easily changes these values. Or use the setters provided. Default values are:
        • mMinGoodRating - 3 - DefaultOnUserSelectedRatingListener.DEFAULT_MIN_GOOD_RATING
        • mNegativeButtonText - No Thanks - R.string.ratetheapp_negative_button
        • mPositiveButtonText - Sure - R.string.ratetheapp_positive_button
        • mGoodRatingTitle - Thanks! - R.string.ratetheapp_goodrating_title
        • mGoodRatingMessage - Thanks so much! Would you mind rating us or leaving a review at the App Store? - R.string.ratetheapp_goodrating_text
        • mBadRatingTitle - Hi There! - R.string.ratetheapp_badrating_title
        • mBadRatingMessage - I’m really sorry to hear that you don’t like our app. Would you mind sending me your thoughts on how we can improve the app? I’ll respond directly. Thanks for your help. - R.string.ratetheapp_badrating_text
        • mFeedbackEmailSubject - App Feedback: Android - R.string.ratetheapp_feedback_subject
        • mFeedbackEmailMessage - null
        Parameters:
        emailTo - String
        Returns:
        DefaultOnUserSelectedRatingListener
